countries","startTime":null,"eventDescription":"Leaving Countries, in both sound and mantra, is a songwriter’s tribute to the crossroads between life on the road and the affinity of home in the Georgia heartland. Founded in 2007 by Atlanta Institute of Music graduate Louis Phillip Pelot, the band’s original repertoire is a genuinely Southern perspective on traditional country and American folk music.

The band went on tour beginning in 2010, and has played hundreds of shows each year, traveling on two national tours and sharing the journey with artists including American Nomad, Dum Spiro Spero, and Jeremy Arndt. After settling in Athens, Georgia to raise a family, Pelot soon began to channel his passion for live music into booking other artists and connecting them with local venues, as well as performing on nearly every stage in town.
 
In the years since, the thoughtfully crafted lyrics and authenticity of the music have become as attractive to other musicians as it has to fans, resulting in an often shifting lineup of performers from a wide range of styles and genres. Throughout, the story of Leaving Countries has been told in many artistic languages, the dynamic blend of interpretations perfectly in balance with the continuity of the inspirations that guide it.
